law.text:
If a person who generates a controlled hazardous substance desires to have it transported to a controlled hazardous substance facility, the person:
Except as is otherwise required by federal or State law, shall label the controlled hazardous substance as required by the rules and regulations of the Department;
Shall provide for each controlled hazardous substance vehicle a manifest that describes the controlled hazardous substance, including volume and chemical, physical, and biological characteristics;
Shall require evidence of a hauler certificate and a vehicle certificate;
May contract for treatment, storage, or disposal of a controlled hazardous substance only with:
A facility permit holder; or
A controlled hazardous substance hauler who has a valid contract with a controlled hazardous substance facility for treatment, storage, or disposal of controlled hazardous substances; and
Shall report, from time to time on the form the Department requires, the following information about shipments of controlled hazardous substances:
Source;
Name of the controlled hazardous substance hauler;
Destination intended by the controlled hazardous substance hauler at the time of shipment;
Volume; and
Nature.
